    <note>Han(1) Hui [22453] QTW, 507.4a-8a; JTS, 129.8a; XTS, 126.27a; ZZTJ, 226.7279. According to this, 8th generation ancestor, Bo [22444], moved to Yingchuan, which became the ancestral home of the lineage. XTS, 73A.9a has him moving to Changli, Jicheng. Jicheng is another name for Jize, which is located in Xuzhou (Yingchuan), Changge county, whereas the only identifications for Changli are in the area of modern Beijing. The only conclusion, which resolves many difficulties, is that Changli was a name for Yingchuan and Bo moved to the migration target of collateral ancestor, Xin [22437], during the Later Han dynasty! On the other hand, Bo may have moved first to Changli in area of Beijing and then to Jicheng or Yingchuan. This explains the identification of Han(1) Yu [3332] as a Yingchuan Han(1) as well as additional explanation for the Song Nanyang Han(1) using Xuzhou, Xuchang county as their burial site. It also establishes a close connection between the Han(1), who call themselves Changli Han(1), Yingchuan Han(1) and Nanyang Han(1).From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:780:  From Jianyi dafu, apt. Hubu shilang, Pan Duzhi</note>
